ğŸ“Œ Project Overview
Manual blood cell analysis under a microscope is time-consuming, error-prone, and requires expert intervention. This project automates the detection 
and counting of blood cells from microscopic images using deep learningâ€“based object detection.
The model accurately identifies and counts different blood cell types, helping reduce human effort and improving efficiency in medical image analysis.

ğŸ¯ Problem Statement

1) Traditional blood cell counting is done manually by lab technicians
2) High chances of human error
3) Not scalable for large datasets
4) Requires significant time and expertise

Solution:
Use computer vision and deep learning to automatically detect and count blood cells from images.

ğŸš€ Features

1) Automatic detection of blood cells from images
2) Bounding box visualization for detected cells
3) Accurate cell counting
4) Trained using state-of-the-art object detection model
5) Scalable for real-world medical datasets

ğŸ§  Tech Stack

1) Programming Language: Python
